Pre-Chat Forms and Post-Chat Pages in Service Cloud

Pre-chat forms and post-chat pages enable you to exchange information with customers who contact your company through chat.

Available in: Salesforce Classic, Performance Editions, Developer Edition orgs created after June 14, 2012, Unlimited Edition, and Enterprise Edition with Service Cloud.

The legacy chat product is scheduled for retirement on February 14, 2026. Pre-chat forms and post-chat pages offer a standardized way of collecting information from customers before and sharing information with them after their chat sessions are finished. You can also use this information to customize the chat experience for your users.

By using pre-chat forms, you can collect information from a customer, such as a name or description of a problem, and direct chat requests efficiently. By using post-chat pages, you can share information with customers at the end of a chat session, such as directing them to another Web page or forwarding them to a survey.

You have to create pre-chat forms and post-chat pages programmatically using Chat's APIs. See the Chat Developer Guide for more information.
